						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Vīrapāṇḍya, 35th year = A.D. 1331.</p>						

						<p>This much worn out inscription refers to a peace compact between some <hi rend="italic">araiya</hi> members of Pūvarasakuḻi and some others agreeing to be friendly towards one another. Some of the <hi rend="italic">araiyas</hi> were Īḻattaraiyaṉ, Ulagamāṇikkapparaiyaṉ, Māvalivāṇādarāyaṉ, and Iḍaiyaṉ Iruṅgōḷan.</p>						

						</summary>
